  "informal_statement": "If 3 items are each placed into one of 2 boxes (modeled as a function from {0,1,2} into {0,1}), some two distinct items land in the same box — the pigeonhole principle's simplest concrete instance.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Directly `Finset.exists_ne_map_eq_of_card_lt_of_maps_to`, discharging the cardinality comparison `(Finset.range 2).card < (Finset.range 3).card` by `decide`.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem pigeonhole_3_into_2 (f : ℕ → ℕ) (hf : ∀ a ∈ Finset.range 3, f a ∈ Finset.range 2) : ∃ x ∈ Finset.range 3, ∃ y ∈ Finset.range 3, x ≠ y ∧ f x = f y",
